Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Orientale is one of the 10 provinces of the Democratic Republic of the Congo. Orientale Province lies in the north east of the country. It borders Equateur to the west, Kasai-Oriental province to the south west, Maniema to the south, and Nord-Kivu to the south east. The province is divided into the Bas-Uele, Haut-Uele, and Tshopo districts and the Ituri Interim Administration. The current suspected outbreak, now unconfirmed, is located some 240 km [150 mi] distant from the previously confined outbreak in Orientale province in late 2012.

Further information is awaited on the outcome of the current investigation.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the Democratic Republic of Congo can be seen at http://healthmap.org/r/735b. A map showing the location of Orientale Province can be accessed at http://www.pbs.org/wnet/wideangle/episodes/democracy-in-the-rough/map-elections-2006-places-politics-and-players/province-orientale/1657/. - Mod.CP]
